  "prompt": "What is it like to live in New Mexico?",
  "response": "Living in New Mexico offers a unique experience with several distinctive characteristics:\n\n1. Climate\n- Mostly dry, desert-like climate\n- Hot summers and mild winters\n- Low humidity\n- Lots of sunshine\n- Significant temperature variations between day and night\n\n2. Landscape\n- Diverse terrain including deserts, mountains, and forests\n- Beautiful landscapes with unique rock formations\n- Stunning sunsets and wide-open skies\n- Rich in natural beauty\n\n3. Culture\n- Strong Native American and Hispanic influences\n- Vibrant arts scene, especially in Santa Fe\n- Rich cultural heritage and traditions\n- Unique cuisine featuring green and red chile\n- Friendly and relaxed lifestyle\n\n4. Cost of Living\n- Generally more affordable compared to coastal states\n- Lower housing prices\n- Lower overall cost of living\n\n5. Outdoor Activities\n- Excellent for hiking, skiing, mountain biking\n- National parks and monuments\n- Great for outdoor enthusiasts\n- Proximity to national forests\n\n6. Economy\n- Government and military jobs are significant\n- Growing tech and film industries\n- Agriculture and tourism are important sectors\n\n7. Challenges\n- Limited job market in some areas\n- Rural areas can be relatively isolated\n- Some parts of the state have high poverty rates",
